  "Question": "<p>The limit I need to calculate is <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_534\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{(x,y)\\rightarrow(0,0)}\\frac{xy^{2}}{x^{4}+y^{2}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Using polar coordinates I get: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_535\"><math alttext=\"lim_{r\\rightarrow 0}\\frac{r\\cos(\\theta)\\sin^{2}(\\theta)}{r^{2}\\cos^{4}(\\theta)% +\\sin^{2}(\\theta)}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>l</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Now if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_536\"><math alttext=\"\\sin(\\theta)\\neq 0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2260</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> then the limit is <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_537\"><math alttext=\"0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mn>0</mn></semantics></math></span>. How do I handle the case where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_538\"><math alttext=\"\\theta=0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> or <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_539\"><math alttext=\"\\theta=\\pi\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>? And is there a better way to approach this limit?</p>",
  "Title": "limit with two variables",
